# Before Every Implementation

Produce a plan **before writing code**. Use the `feature-implementation` skill for the full template.

## Required Plan Flow

```text
Feature
  ↓
Requirements
  ↓
Architecture
  ↓
Files to change
  ↓
Database changes
  ↓
API changes
  ↓
Frontend changes
  ↓
Testing plan
  ↓
Implementation
  ↓
Review
```

## Plan Must Include

1. Business requirement and acceptance criteria
2. Affected modules and layer boundaries
3. Security, performance, and cost considerations
4. Explicit file list (create / modify)
5. Migration or schema changes (if any)
6. Test strategy (unit, integration, E2E)
7. Documentation updates required

Do not skip planning for "small" changes — small leaks become architectural debt.
